1
00:00:01,209 --> 00:00:02,878
<b>[birds chirping]</b>

2
00:00:06,465 --> 00:00:07,633
<b>[Fujisawa gasps]</b>

3
00:00:12,638 --> 00:00:16,224
<b>[NAO] Mr. Fujisawa, you're not
getting away with this.</b>

4
00:00:16,266 --> 00:00:17,392
<b>[Fujisawa gasps softly]</b>

5
00:00:17,434 --> 00:00:18,435
<b>[NAO] From now on,</b>

6
00:00:18,477 --> 00:00:20,896
<b>I'm taking
the Liar Game seriously.</b>

7
00:00:21,104 --> 00:00:22,189
<b>Also...</b>

8
00:00:22,815 --> 00:00:25,818
<b>I'm not only getting back
my 100 million yen.</b>

9
00:00:25,860 --> 00:00:28,069
<b>I'm going to steal yours
as well.</b>

10
00:00:28,654 --> 00:00:31,490
<b>By the end,
I'll be declared the winner!</b>

11
00:00:33,283 --> 00:00:35,786
<b>[♪ opening theme song playing]</b>

12
00:02:03,206 --> 00:02:05,584
<b>SHOCKWAVE</b>

13
00:02:05,626 --> 00:02:08,169
<b>[Fujisawa groans]</b>

14
00:02:09,504 --> 00:02:11,757
<b>[NAO] I'd made up my mind
to fight back.</b>

15
00:02:11,799 --> 00:02:14,342
<b>Moping and crying
wouldn't get me anywhere.</b>

16
00:02:14,384 --> 00:02:16,344
<b>I needed to do something,</b>

17
00:02:16,386 --> 00:02:18,889
<b>and I'd found
the perfect ally to help me.</b>

18
00:02:18,931 --> 00:02:20,390
<b>I have a plan.</b>

19
00:02:20,891 --> 00:02:22,977
<b>[NAO] Somehow,
a brilliant con artist</b>

20
00:02:23,018 --> 00:02:24,979
<b>who brought down
a corrupt corporation</b>

21
00:02:25,020 --> 00:02:26,480
<b>was standing in my corner.</b>

22
00:02:26,521 --> 00:02:28,774
<b>He was bound to know
the right thing to do.</b>

23
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:32,527
<b>Your plan... What is it?</b>

24
00:02:32,903 --> 00:02:35,322
<b>We only need to do two things.</b>

25
00:02:35,363 --> 00:02:36,573
<b>Follow these steps,</b>

26
00:02:36,615 --> 00:02:38,826
<b>and I guarantee
we'll get the money back.</b>

27
00:02:39,910 --> 00:02:43,371
<b>Step one, tell him that
you're playing the Liar Game,</b>

28
00:02:43,413 --> 00:02:45,791
<b>and be sure
to make it sound convincing.</b>

29
00:02:46,041 --> 00:02:47,501
<b>As for the second step,</b>

30
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:50,462
<b>keep him under
constant surveillance.</b>

31
00:02:50,754 --> 00:02:52,255
<b>Is that all?</b>

32
00:02:52,297 --> 00:02:53,757
<b>That's the whole plan?</b>

33
00:02:53,799 --> 00:02:55,884
<b>Yes. Trust me.</b>

34
00:02:57,886 --> 00:02:59,972
<b>[NAO] That's why
I confronted Mr. Fujisawa</b>

35
00:03:00,014 --> 00:03:02,307
<b>and told him my intentions
to win the game.</b>

36
00:03:02,349 --> 00:03:05,060
<b>And why I began to monitor him.</b>

37
00:03:06,227 --> 00:03:10,983
<b>Still, is this really enough
to get me the 200 million yen?</b>

38
00:03:15,696 --> 00:03:16,655
<b>[Fujisawa gasps]</b>

39
00:03:16,697 --> 00:03:17,739
<b>It's you.</b>

40
00:03:20,325 --> 00:03:21,618
<b>Hello again.</b>

41
00:03:21,660 --> 00:03:23,120
<b>I just want to let you know</b>

42
00:03:23,162 --> 00:03:26,040
<b>that I'll be playing too,
on Ms. Kanzaki's behalf,</b>

43
00:03:26,081 --> 00:03:28,125
<b>of course, in case
there was any doubt.</b>

44
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:32,295
<b>Which means that I'll soon be
taking 200 million yen from you.</b>

45
00:03:32,337 --> 00:03:33,588
<b>That understood?</b>

46
00:03:33,630 --> 00:03:36,800
<b>[grunts] Ha!
You're never going to get it!</b>

47
00:03:36,842 --> 00:03:38,259
<b>-Are you sure?
-[gasps]</b>

48
00:03:38,552 --> 00:03:39,803
<b>Believe it or not,</b>

49
00:03:39,928 --> 00:03:42,723
<b>I have a perfect plan
to steal the money for her.</b>

50
00:03:42,764 --> 00:03:44,265
<b>[Fujisawa exclaims]</b>

51
00:03:44,307 --> 00:03:46,309
<b>[Fujisawa pants]</b>

52
00:03:47,644 --> 00:03:49,188
<b>[door opens]</b>

53
00:03:49,563 --> 00:03:50,772
<b>[door closes]</b>

54
00:03:56,528 --> 00:03:58,822
<b>[Fujisawa groans]</b>

55
00:03:58,864 --> 00:04:01,240
<b>Good evening.
Is this the police?</b>

56
00:04:01,282 --> 00:04:03,451
<b>A suspicious vehicle
has been parked</b>

57
00:04:03,493 --> 00:04:05,579
<b>outside my house for a while.</b>

58
00:04:07,039 --> 00:04:08,247
<b>[NAO] Huh?</b>

59
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:12,251
<b>No way! The police?</b>

60
00:04:17,382 --> 00:04:20,094
<b>[chuckles] Wait, you let
the cops scare you off?</b>

61
00:04:20,135 --> 00:04:22,096
<b>How was I supposed to react?</b>

62
00:04:22,137 --> 00:04:24,305
<b>-You're right. Sorry.
-[Nao gasps]</b>

63
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:33,314
<b>[AKIYAMA] I figured something
like that might happen.</b>

64
00:04:33,774 --> 00:04:34,858
<b>With that in mind,</b>

65
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:36,902
<b>I've leased this apartment
for a month.</b>

66
00:04:37,527 --> 00:04:39,446
<b>-Have a look out the window.
-Huh?</b>

67
00:04:42,616 --> 00:04:44,409
<b>Oh, it's my teacher's house!</b>

68
00:04:44,451 --> 00:04:46,036
<b>Now we can watch him from here</b>

69
00:04:46,078 --> 00:04:48,830
<b>without having to worry
about the cops bothering us.</b>

70
00:04:51,625 --> 00:04:54,878
<b>[NAO] Thank you, Mr. Akiyama.
You're a good person.</b>

71
00:04:56,088 --> 00:04:59,174
<b>At first, I thought you were
scary and intimidating.</b>

72
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,635
<b>But you've been
nothing but kind,</b>

73
00:05:01,676 --> 00:05:02,844
<b>scheduling our shifts</b>

74
00:05:02,886 --> 00:05:04,972
<b>so I can visit my father
in the hospital.</b>

75
00:05:05,013 --> 00:05:07,975
<b>You even went through
the trouble to rent this place.</b>

76
00:05:09,810 --> 00:05:12,562
<b>Please tell me, what reason
do you have to help me</b>

77
00:05:12,604 --> 00:05:13,981
<b>right after your release?</b>

78
00:05:16,150 --> 00:05:17,859
<b>Money, obviously.</b>

79
00:05:17,901 --> 00:05:19,736
<b>Companies would be
out of their mind</b>

80
00:05:19,778 --> 00:05:22,656
<b>to hire an ex-conman
as an employee after what I did.</b>

81
00:05:23,907 --> 00:05:25,993
<b>If I steal the full 200 million
for you,</b>

82
00:05:26,034 --> 00:05:27,619
<b>then I get a quarter of it.</b>

83
00:05:27,661 --> 00:05:29,913
<b>Fifty million
for a month's work?</b>

84
00:05:30,329 --> 00:05:32,499
<b>I'd be crazy to pass that up.</b>

85
00:05:36,211 --> 00:05:39,214
<b>ONE WEEK LATER</b>

86
00:05:39,631 --> 00:05:40,966
<b>[NAO] This was all assuming</b>

87
00:05:41,008 --> 00:05:43,342
<b>that we would successfully
steal the money.</b>

88
00:05:43,802 --> 00:05:46,554
<b>Why was he so confident
that we could actually do it?</b>

89
00:05:46,596 --> 00:05:48,932
<b>-[door opens]
-[AKIYAMA] Time to switch out.</b>

90
00:05:52,602 --> 00:05:54,896
<b>Anything out of the ordinary
today?</b>

91
00:05:54,938 --> 00:05:56,523
<b>Doesn't look like it.</b>

92
00:05:56,773 --> 00:05:59,442
<b>Early on, he'd go
to the pachinko parlor</b>

93
00:05:59,484 --> 00:06:00,902
<b>or pick up his groceries.</b>

94
00:06:00,944 --> 00:06:03,446
<b>But he hasn't even left
the house these past few days,</b>

95
00:06:03,488 --> 00:06:04,906
<b>so it's been quiet.</b>

96
00:06:04,948 --> 00:06:06,325
<b>Interesting.</b>

97
00:06:06,992 --> 00:06:08,576
<b>-[NAO] Um...
-[AKIYAMA] Hm?</b>

98
00:06:08,952 --> 00:06:11,288
<b>Can you tell me
what the point of all this is,</b>

99
00:06:11,330 --> 00:06:12,831
<b>if you don't mind me asking?</b>

100
00:06:12,873 --> 00:06:14,249
<b>-[AKIYAMA] Hm?
-So far,</b>

101
00:06:14,291 --> 00:06:15,667
<b>we've spent the entire week</b>

102
00:06:15,709 --> 00:06:17,961
<b>doing nothing
but staring at his house.</b>

103
00:06:18,003 --> 00:06:20,297
<b>I don't mean to doubt you.</b>

104
00:06:20,339 --> 00:06:23,050
<b>I just don't know
what we're trying to accomplish.</b>

105
00:06:24,509 --> 00:06:26,970
<b>[AKIYAMA] What we're doing
is conman 101.</b>

106
00:06:27,512 --> 00:06:30,515
<b>"Before springing your trap,
try to rattle your target."</b>

107
00:06:30,557 --> 00:06:31,766
<b>Weaken them.</b>

108
00:06:31,975 --> 00:06:35,478
<b>For example, bank transfer
scams against the elderly.</b>

109
00:06:36,146 --> 00:06:38,273
<b>The scammers will impersonate
a loved one</b>

110
00:06:38,315 --> 00:06:40,650
<b>panicking about money
over the phone.</b>

111
00:06:40,692 --> 00:06:42,069
<b>So old people freak out</b>

112
00:06:42,110 --> 00:06:44,738
<b>and open up the floodgates
to their finances.</b>

113
00:06:45,364 --> 00:06:47,532
<b>You could be as level-headed
as they come,</b>

114
00:06:47,574 --> 00:06:49,284
<b>but as soon as you lose
your composure</b>

115
00:06:49,326 --> 00:06:52,411
<b>and start to waver,
you become a much easier mark.</b>

116
00:06:52,453 --> 00:06:54,789
<b>In short, your former teacher...</b>

117
00:06:54,831 --> 00:06:57,000
<b>We're going to drive him
to the brink mentally</b>

118
00:06:57,042 --> 00:06:58,126
<b>until he cracks.</b>

119
00:06:58,168 --> 00:06:59,336
<b>[Nao gasps]</b>

120
00:06:59,378 --> 00:07:01,922
<b>Imagine if you were
in his situation.</b>

121
00:07:01,963 --> 00:07:04,716
<b>His opponent declared
that she would win to his face,</b>

122
00:07:04,758 --> 00:07:06,968
<b>then I told him that
I had the perfect plan</b>

123
00:07:07,010 --> 00:07:08,803
<b>to steal the 200 million.</b>

124
00:07:09,346 --> 00:07:11,472
<b>But he has no idea
what the plan is,</b>

125
00:07:11,514 --> 00:07:14,809
<b>and on top of that
is under 24-hour surveillance.</b>

126
00:07:15,352 --> 00:07:17,312
<b>-See for yourself.
-Uh?</b>

127
00:07:20,439 --> 00:07:21,691
<b>They say they've got a plan,</b>

128
00:07:21,733 --> 00:07:23,318
<b>but that would require
getting the money</b>

129
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:24,694
<b>from where I've got it stashed.</b>

130
00:07:24,736 --> 00:07:26,571
<b>So what the hell
could they have up their sleeve?</b>

131
00:07:26,613 --> 00:07:28,907
<b>Downright impossible,
there's no way they can do it.</b>

132
00:07:28,949 --> 00:07:31,618
<b>Besides, I've got
a perfect plan of my own.</b>

133
00:07:31,659 --> 00:07:32,702
<b>[Fujisawa gasps]</b>

134
00:07:32,744 --> 00:07:34,037
<b>[exclaims]</b>

135
00:07:35,372 --> 00:07:36,748
<b>Well then?</b>

136
00:07:36,873 --> 00:07:39,751
<b>He definitely looks like
he's flustered and more on edge.</b>

137
00:07:39,793 --> 00:07:41,002
<b>[Akiyama chuckles]</b>

138
00:07:41,044 --> 00:07:43,504
<b>Yeah, knowing someone's
watching you all day</b>

139
00:07:43,546 --> 00:07:45,799
<b>and all night is bound
to take its toll on a person.</b>

140
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:48,593
<b>The psychological pressure
keeps building up</b>

141
00:07:48,635 --> 00:07:50,804
<b>with each passing second.</b>

142
00:07:52,431 --> 00:07:54,141
<b>[NAO] All right,
now I understand</b>

143
00:07:54,182 --> 00:07:56,184
<b>that the goal is
to break him down.</b>

144
00:07:56,226 --> 00:07:57,352
<b>However...</b>

145
00:07:57,394 --> 00:08:00,355
<b>How is that supposed
to get us the money?</b>

146
00:08:00,397 --> 00:08:03,108
<b>He's got it stashed away
in a safe deposit box,</b>

147
00:08:03,150 --> 00:08:04,443
<b>which means
we won't get anywhere</b>

148
00:08:04,483 --> 00:08:06,320
<b>till we figure out
which bank he's using!</b>

149
00:08:06,361 --> 00:08:07,446
<b>And even if we knew,</b>

150
00:08:07,737 --> 00:08:09,614
<b>we only have a two-day window
to steal it from him</b>

151
00:08:09,656 --> 00:08:11,325
<b>before the game ends!</b>

152
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:15,287
<b>He may not be keeping the money
in a bank in the first place.</b>

153
00:08:15,329 --> 00:08:16,455
<b>[NAO] Huh?</b>

154
00:08:16,495 --> 00:08:18,206
<b>I'll get right to the point.</b>

155
00:08:18,790 --> 00:08:22,461
<b>The 200 million yen,
it's in his house.</b>

156
00:08:22,669 --> 00:08:23,920
<b>[Nao gasps]</b>

157
00:08:23,962 --> 00:08:26,214
<b>Really? What makes you say that?</b>

158
00:08:26,256 --> 00:08:27,757
<b>Just think about it.</b>

159
00:08:27,799 --> 00:08:30,844
<b>Imagine you've got 200 million
you want to hold onto,</b>

160
00:08:30,885 --> 00:08:34,139
<b>so you go to the bank and put it
in a safe deposit box.</b>

161
00:08:34,181 --> 00:08:36,933
<b>Meanwhile, your enemies
are spying on you and your home</b>

162
00:08:36,975 --> 00:08:38,352
<b>during all hours of the day,</b>

163
00:08:38,477 --> 00:08:40,937
<b>waiting for the perfect
opportunity to make their move.</b>

164
00:08:40,979 --> 00:08:42,939
<b>What's your move?</b>

165
00:08:43,398 --> 00:08:46,985
<b>I'd leave my house immediately,
and stay far away.</b>

166
00:08:47,277 --> 00:08:48,653
<b>Why's that?</b>

167
00:08:49,446 --> 00:08:50,655
<b>Because I couldn't bear</b>

168
00:08:50,697 --> 00:08:52,740
<b>the thought of always
being watched.</b>

169
00:08:52,782 --> 00:08:54,659
<b>The stress would overwhelm me.</b>

170
00:08:55,285 --> 00:08:57,245
<b>The money's in the bank already,</b>

171
00:08:57,287 --> 00:09:00,081
<b>so I'm better off staying
mentally and physically sharp</b>

172
00:09:00,123 --> 00:09:01,500
<b>for the end of the game.</b>

173
00:09:01,540 --> 00:09:03,001
<b>That makes sense.</b>

174
00:09:03,335 --> 00:09:05,420
<b>But what if you chose
not to hide</b>

175
00:09:05,462 --> 00:09:06,963
<b>the 200 million in a bank?</b>

176
00:09:07,005 --> 00:09:09,341
<b>What if you hid it
in some bushes instead?</b>

177
00:09:09,383 --> 00:09:11,926
<b>[gasps] Then I definitely
wouldn't just sit around</b>

178
00:09:11,968 --> 00:09:13,011
<b>at my place!</b>

179
00:09:13,428 --> 00:09:15,596
<b>I'd want to be in a spot where
I could always watch it!</b>

180
00:09:15,638 --> 00:09:17,182
<b>That so?</b>

181
00:09:17,224 --> 00:09:20,185
<b>Out there, it's vulnerable
to getting stolen</b>

182
00:09:20,227 --> 00:09:22,062
<b>if someone finds out
where it is.</b>

183
00:09:22,103 --> 00:09:24,022
<b>It doesn't even
have to be an opponent.</b>

184
00:09:24,064 --> 00:09:26,233
<b>Some stranger could randomly
come across the money</b>

185
00:09:26,274 --> 00:09:27,817
<b>and take it for themselves.</b>

186
00:09:27,859 --> 00:09:29,152
<b>How strange then.</b>

187
00:09:29,361 --> 00:09:32,113
<b>He claims the money's sitting
safe in a bank somewhere,</b>

188
00:09:32,155 --> 00:09:33,365
<b>yet he's at home?</b>

189
00:09:33,407 --> 00:09:34,491
<b>[Nao gasps]</b>

190
00:09:34,908 --> 00:09:36,910
<b>[AKIYAMA] He knows he's under
constant surveillance,</b>

191
00:09:36,951 --> 00:09:38,953
<b>so much so that
he's unraveling.</b>

192
00:09:38,995 --> 00:09:40,747
<b>If the money's actually safe,</b>

193
00:09:40,788 --> 00:09:42,581
<b>why put himself through this?</b>

194
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:45,210
<b>There's only one explanation.</b>

195
00:09:45,502 --> 00:09:48,338
<b>The 200 million
never actually left his house,</b>

196
00:09:48,380 --> 00:09:50,507
<b>and he's worried
that we might steal it.</b>

197
00:09:50,549 --> 00:09:51,841
<b>Wait, you're right!</b>

198
00:09:52,133 --> 00:09:54,261
<b>If the money's just been hidden
in his house all this time,</b>

199
00:09:54,302 --> 00:09:56,263
<b>he wouldn't dare leave it
unattended,</b>

200
00:09:56,304 --> 00:09:59,099
<b>not when he knows we're tracking
everything he's doing!</b>

201
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:00,350
<b>[chuckles] Say...</b>

202
00:10:00,392 --> 00:10:02,394
<b>Might be time we turn up
the heat even more</b>

203
00:10:02,436 --> 00:10:05,188
<b>with our surveillance tactics,
to keep him on his toes.</b>

204
00:10:05,772 --> 00:10:07,274
<b>We'll make it abundantly clear</b>

205
00:10:07,315 --> 00:10:10,485
<b>we know where the money's
been hidden this entire time.</b>

206
00:10:10,902 --> 00:10:11,986
<b>Okay!</b>

207
00:10:12,028 --> 00:10:13,154
<b>♪</b>

208
00:10:13,572 --> 00:10:15,073
<b>LIAR GAME ENDS IN 16 DAYS</b>

209
00:10:15,115 --> 00:10:16,866
<b>[NAO] The pressure
must have gotten to him.</b>

210
00:10:16,908 --> 00:10:20,328
<b>Mr. Fujisawa's anxiety
was right on his face.</b>

211
00:10:20,370 --> 00:10:23,373
<b>He moved around the house
even less than he did before.</b>

212
00:10:23,415 --> 00:10:24,665
<b>♪</b>

213
00:10:25,459 --> 00:10:27,335
<b>He hasn't moved.</b>

214
00:10:27,377 --> 00:10:29,963
<b>I don't think he's even shifted
more than an inch.</b>

215
00:10:30,004 --> 00:10:33,632
<b>Oh. That helps
narrow down the location.</b>

216
00:10:35,385 --> 00:10:36,844
<b>[birds chirping]</b>

217
00:10:37,387 --> 00:10:40,557
<b>[NAO] Which room could he have
stashed the money in?</b>

218
00:10:41,682 --> 00:10:43,143
<b>Technically, he could've split</b>

219
00:10:43,184 --> 00:10:45,937
<b>the 200 million up across
different rooms.</b>

220
00:10:45,979 --> 00:10:47,272
<b>If he really wanted to,</b>

221
00:10:47,314 --> 00:10:49,648
<b>he could've even split it up
thousands of times</b>

222
00:10:49,690 --> 00:10:51,234
<b>across his whole house!</b>

223
00:10:51,485 --> 00:10:52,860
<b>[Nao groans]</b>

224
00:10:52,902 --> 00:10:54,779
<b>Nao, is everything all right?</b>

225
00:10:54,821 --> 00:10:57,031
<b>[NAO] Yes!
Don't worry about a thing!</b>

226
00:10:58,866 --> 00:11:00,868
<b>[NAO] I have to win this game.</b>

227
00:11:00,910 --> 00:11:03,704
<b>Not for me, but for Father!</b>

228
00:11:04,331 --> 00:11:07,083
<b>LIAR GAME ENDS IN 10 DAYS</b>

229
00:11:11,546 --> 00:11:14,633
<b>Just look at him.
Not looking good, is he?</b>

230
00:11:15,383 --> 00:11:18,595
<b>A perfect time
to mess with him even more.</b>

231
00:11:21,097 --> 00:11:23,057
<b>[gas hissing]</b>

232
00:11:23,891 --> 00:11:24,976
<b>[Fujisawa gasps]</b>

233
00:11:25,018 --> 00:11:27,312
<b>It smells like
something is burning.</b>

234
00:11:27,354 --> 00:11:29,897
<b>Where is all the smoke
coming from?</b>

235
00:11:30,357 --> 00:11:32,150
<b>-[explosion]
-[Fujisawa gasps]</b>

236
00:11:32,192 --> 00:11:34,277
<b>Was that an explosion?
What's going on?</b>

237
00:11:35,069 --> 00:11:37,238
<b>Did something catch on fire
in the kitchen?</b>

238
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:38,365
<b>Is it the stove?</b>

239
00:11:38,406 --> 00:11:39,740
<b>Maybe the tub?</b>

240
00:11:39,782 --> 00:11:41,242
<b>Or the water heater?</b>

241
00:11:41,284 --> 00:11:42,661
<b>[Fujisawa exclaims]</b>

242
00:11:42,994 --> 00:11:44,245
<b>Damn it all.</b>

243
00:11:47,915 --> 00:11:50,001
<b>-[dial tone]
-[Fujisawa groans]</b>

244
00:11:50,043 --> 00:11:51,294
<b>Hey, Tanaka.</b>

245
00:11:51,336 --> 00:11:52,671
<b>Yeah, it's Fujisawa.</b>

246
00:11:52,711 --> 00:11:54,255
<b>Something's burning in my house,</b>

247
00:11:54,297 --> 00:11:56,174
<b>and I need you to drop
whatever you're doing</b>

248
00:11:56,216 --> 00:11:57,758
<b>and come help me find out what.</b>

249
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:59,844
<b>And hurry,
there's smoke everywhere.</b>

250
00:12:00,887 --> 00:12:03,181
<b>Why would I call a fire truck?
I called you!</b>

251
00:12:03,223 --> 00:12:05,141
<b>-[laughter]
-[Fujisawa gasps]</b>

252
00:12:05,183 --> 00:12:07,352
<b>[AKIYAMA] You should listen
to your friend.</b>

253
00:12:07,394 --> 00:12:09,270
<b>The whole point
of the fire department</b>

254
00:12:09,312 --> 00:12:11,105
<b>is to call them
when there's a fire.</b>

255
00:12:11,147 --> 00:12:14,942
<b>Granted, the "fire" you heard
was my new toy here.</b>

256
00:12:15,610 --> 00:12:16,777
<b>The smoke was real, though.</b>

257
00:12:16,819 --> 00:12:18,446
<b>It was coming through
your outside vent,</b>

258
00:12:18,488 --> 00:12:20,031
<b>if you're still curious.</b>

259
00:12:20,073 --> 00:12:23,660
<b>Gotta say, I'm more curious
about how you reacted.</b>

260
00:12:23,702 --> 00:12:25,078
<b>Instead of racing
around the house</b>

261
00:12:25,119 --> 00:12:26,413
<b>and calling
the fire department,</b>

262
00:12:26,454 --> 00:12:28,331
<b>you stayed put
and called a friend.</b>

263
00:12:28,373 --> 00:12:30,458
<b>It's almost like
you'd rather be burned alive</b>

264
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:32,335
<b>than take one step
outside this room.</b>

265
00:12:32,377 --> 00:12:34,421
<b>But that's just crazy, right?</b>

266
00:12:34,462 --> 00:12:35,838
<b>[Fujisawa groans]</b>

267
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:36,964
<b>[Akiyama chuckles]</b>

268
00:12:37,006 --> 00:12:38,341
<b>Unless, of course,</b>

269
00:12:38,383 --> 00:12:40,968
<b>you've got all of the game money
stashed in there.</b>

270
00:12:41,010 --> 00:12:42,429
<b>[FUJISAWA] You can't know that!</b>

271
00:12:42,470 --> 00:12:45,599
<b>Oh, we knew you hid it
somewhere in the house.</b>

272
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:48,685
<b>Finding exactly where
was trickier, but not by much.</b>

273
00:12:48,727 --> 00:12:50,811
<b>We knew if you thought
the money was in danger,</b>

274
00:12:50,853 --> 00:12:53,981
<b>you'd rush to your hiding spot
to make sure it was all right.</b>

275
00:12:54,023 --> 00:12:55,816
<b>[Fujisawa grunts]</b>

276
00:12:56,317 --> 00:12:58,152
<b>[FUJISAWA]
And I stayed right here.</b>

277
00:12:58,194 --> 00:12:59,862
<b>Congratulations, young man.</b>

278
00:12:59,904 --> 00:13:01,906
<b>You got me,
and I was none the wiser.</b>

279
00:13:01,948 --> 00:13:03,700
<b>-[Nao gasps]
-Thank you.</b>

280
00:13:03,991 --> 00:13:05,702
<b>But that's not all, I'm sure.</b>

281
00:13:05,744 --> 00:13:07,161
<b>[Fujisawa laughs]</b>

282
00:13:07,203 --> 00:13:09,788
<b>Oh, you haven't
the faintest idea, young man.</b>

283
00:13:09,830 --> 00:13:12,083
<b>[chuckles]
See, it doesn't matter.</b>

284
00:13:12,125 --> 00:13:15,169
<b>Even if you know where it is,
there's no way this game ends</b>

285
00:13:15,211 --> 00:13:17,796
<b>with you getting
your grubby mitts on it!</b>

286
00:13:18,256 --> 00:13:19,924
<b>My secret weapon!</b>

287
00:13:19,966 --> 00:13:22,302
<b>-[Nao gasps]
-[Fujisawa laughs]</b>

288
00:13:22,343 --> 00:13:24,721
<b>You're as close
as you'll ever get to the money.</b>

289
00:13:24,763 --> 00:13:26,013
<b>Sure, it's not fancy,</b>

290
00:13:26,055 --> 00:13:28,558
<b>but you can't go wrong
with cold, hard steel.</b>

291
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:30,184
<b>You'd need some
heavy-duty equipment</b>

292
00:13:30,226 --> 00:13:31,436
<b>to get through this.</b>

293
00:13:31,770 --> 00:13:34,522
<b>Why, you'd need a forklift
just to get it out of this room!</b>

294
00:13:34,564 --> 00:13:36,483
<b>So, great job
wasting all that time</b>

295
00:13:36,524 --> 00:13:37,816
<b>getting me
to reveal something</b>

296
00:13:37,858 --> 00:13:39,860
<b>that doesn't change
a damn thing!</b>

297
00:13:39,902 --> 00:13:42,238
<b>But you lost a long time ago!</b>

298
00:13:42,280 --> 00:13:43,948
<b>[laughs]</b>

299
00:13:44,574 --> 00:13:46,159
<b>[Nao cries softly]</b>

300
00:13:47,118 --> 00:13:48,827
<b>It's all over?</b>

301
00:13:49,496 --> 00:13:51,331
<b>It can't be.</b>

302
00:13:51,372 --> 00:13:52,624
<b>It's time you quit</b>

303
00:13:52,666 --> 00:13:55,001
<b>this pointless harassment
campaign against me</b>

304
00:13:55,042 --> 00:13:56,877
<b>and start thinking about
how you'll pay back</b>

305
00:13:56,919 --> 00:13:59,838
<b>the 100 million yen debt
you'll have by next week!</b>

306
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:01,924
<b>[Fujisawa laughs]</b>

307
00:14:01,966 --> 00:14:03,092
<b>[Akiyama chuckles]</b>

308
00:14:03,134 --> 00:14:05,094
<b>You're that sure
you've won, huh?</b>

309
00:14:05,136 --> 00:14:06,137
<b>[FUJISAWA] Huh?</b>

310
00:14:06,179 --> 00:14:07,430
<b>[AKIYAMA]
Was flashing your safe</b>

311
00:14:07,472 --> 00:14:09,683
<b>supposed to break
our spirits or something?</b>

312
00:14:09,724 --> 00:14:12,018
<b>Then what? Finally get
a good night's sleep?</b>

313
00:14:12,727 --> 00:14:13,770
<b>That's funny.</b>

314
00:14:13,812 --> 00:14:15,772
<b>-Let me be clear.
-[Fujisawa gasps]</b>

315
00:14:17,565 --> 00:14:18,775
<b>This is nothing.</b>

316
00:14:19,066 --> 00:14:21,944
<b>I can easily empty that safe
right from under your nose.</b>

317
00:14:21,986 --> 00:14:23,196
<b>[Fujisawa gasps]</b>

318
00:14:23,237 --> 00:14:24,489
<b>[Nao gasps]</b>

319
00:14:24,531 --> 00:14:26,907
<b>[FUJISAWA] You... You think
you can rattle me</b>

320
00:14:26,949 --> 00:14:28,702
<b>by spouting
some stupid nonsense?</b>

321
00:14:28,743 --> 00:14:30,161
<b>Well, think again!</b>

322
00:14:30,203 --> 00:14:32,455
<b>There's no way
that you can win!</b>

323
00:14:32,497 --> 00:14:33,665
<b>[Akiyama chuckles]</b>

324
00:14:33,707 --> 00:14:35,709
<b>[AKIYAMA]
Except that there is, though.</b>

325
00:14:35,750 --> 00:14:38,503
<b>And it's really easy, too.</b>

326
00:14:38,545 --> 00:14:39,838
<b>[Fujisawa gasps]</b>

327
00:14:39,878 --> 00:14:41,088
<b>[grunts]</b>

328
00:14:42,799 --> 00:14:45,719
<b>[Fujisawa growls]</b>

329
00:14:46,927 --> 00:14:48,137
<b>[AKIYAMA] You see
how he crumbled</b>

330
00:14:48,179 --> 00:14:49,472
<b>when I pushed back on him?</b>

331
00:14:49,514 --> 00:14:51,683
<b>He was so sure
that we'd give up</b>

332
00:14:51,725 --> 00:14:54,018
<b>the moment we laid eyes
on his safe.</b>

333
00:14:54,060 --> 00:14:56,145
<b>All I had to do was not react</b>

334
00:14:56,187 --> 00:14:59,482
<b>and watch his panic-addled brain
completely shatter.</b>

335
00:14:59,524 --> 00:15:02,068
<b>Just goes to show
how easily we fall</b>

336
00:15:02,109 --> 00:15:03,944
<b>to bias and dissonance.</b>

337
00:15:03,986 --> 00:15:07,114
<b>I know what a bias is,
but what's dissonance?</b>

338
00:15:07,156 --> 00:15:08,533
<b>I've never heard of it.</b>

339
00:15:09,033 --> 00:15:11,745
<b>[AKIYAMA] Let's say you're
asked an A or B question,</b>

340
00:15:11,786 --> 00:15:14,913
<b>and you think A is the answer,
but everyone else thinks it's B.</b>

341
00:15:14,955 --> 00:15:16,957
<b>The stress of being
the odd one out</b>

342
00:15:16,999 --> 00:15:18,376
<b>is a kind of dissonance,</b>

343
00:15:18,418 --> 00:15:19,918
<b>and stress is something
people will do</b>

344
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:21,713
<b>anything to avoid.</b>

345
00:15:21,755 --> 00:15:24,006
<b>Fujisawa was so sure of himself,</b>

346
00:15:24,048 --> 00:15:26,509
<b>his bias made him think
he could break us.</b>

347
00:15:26,551 --> 00:15:28,636
<b>Yet by not reacting
to seeing the safe,</b>

348
00:15:28,678 --> 00:15:30,638
<b>I contradicted that bias.</b>

349
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:32,724
<b>The stress
of that contradiction</b>

350
00:15:32,766 --> 00:15:35,560
<b>put him into a state
of cognitive dissonance.</b>

351
00:15:35,810 --> 00:15:37,270
<b>To deal with that stress,</b>

352
00:15:37,311 --> 00:15:40,022
<b>he changed his bias
to align with my reaction.</b>

353
00:15:40,064 --> 00:15:42,191
<b>[FUJISAWA] He has
another trick up his sleeve!</b>

354
00:15:42,233 --> 00:15:44,444
<b>It's the only thing
that makes sense!</b>

355
00:15:44,485 --> 00:15:46,487
<b>People can be quite malleable</b>

356
00:15:46,529 --> 00:15:48,531
<b>if you give them
the right push.</b>

357
00:15:48,573 --> 00:15:49,574
<b>Do you really know</b>

358
00:15:49,616 --> 00:15:51,284
<b>how to get the money
from the safe?</b>

359
00:15:51,325 --> 00:15:53,202
<b>Because it's starting
to feel like</b>

360
00:15:53,244 --> 00:15:54,412
<b>everything we've been doing</b>

361
00:15:54,829 --> 00:15:57,331
<b>was just to get him to believe
that you had some master plan.</b>

362
00:15:57,373 --> 00:15:59,542
<b>Oh, ye of little faith.</b>

363
00:16:00,752 --> 00:16:03,212
<b>I do, in fact,
have a master plan.</b>

364
00:16:03,254 --> 00:16:06,424
<b>And I know exactly how
to get the money from that safe.</b>

365
00:16:07,717 --> 00:16:10,177
<b>I just can't tell you quite yet.</b>

366
00:16:11,596 --> 00:16:13,013
<b>[NAO] I was still worried,</b>

367
00:16:13,055 --> 00:16:15,182
<b>but trusting him
was my only option.</b>

368
00:16:15,809 --> 00:16:17,560
<b>So, we waited and watched</b>

369
00:16:17,602 --> 00:16:20,647
<b>as Mr. Fujisawa's paranoia
grew and festered.</b>

370
00:16:21,397 --> 00:16:24,191
<b>His occasional odd behaviors
became more frequent</b>

371
00:16:24,233 --> 00:16:25,318
<b>and more odd.</b>

372
00:16:25,610 --> 00:16:27,236
<b>[FUJISAWA]
I know he has a plan.</b>

373
00:16:27,278 --> 00:16:29,530
<b>But what the hell
could it possibly be?</b>

374
00:16:29,572 --> 00:16:32,325
<b>Don't tell me. Could he have
gotten the combination</b>

375
00:16:32,366 --> 00:16:34,076
<b>to the safe somehow?</b>

376
00:16:34,118 --> 00:16:36,329
<b>No, no, no, that can't be it!</b>

377
00:16:36,370 --> 00:16:38,038
<b>Where would he have learned it?</b>

378
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:40,583
<b>Besides, even if he had,
it wouldn't help him.</b>

379
00:16:40,625 --> 00:16:42,376
<b>This safe needs
both a combination</b>

380
00:16:42,418 --> 00:16:43,628
<b>and a key to open it.</b>

381
00:16:43,878 --> 00:16:47,548
<b>And he'll only get that
if he pries it from my corpse.</b>

382
00:16:47,590 --> 00:16:50,969
<b>There's no conceivable way
for him to open this safe.</b>

383
00:16:51,009 --> 00:16:53,387
<b>Unless he breaks it open
by force!</b>

384
00:16:53,429 --> 00:16:55,222
<b>[gasps] That must be it!</b>

385
00:16:55,264 --> 00:16:57,099
<b>But how is he gonna
pull that off?</b>

386
00:16:57,141 --> 00:16:58,559
<b>He can't pry it open.</b>

387
00:16:58,601 --> 00:17:00,561
<b>It's far too thick
and sturdy for that.</b>

388
00:17:00,603 --> 00:17:02,146
<b>But then,
if he'd gotten a hold</b>

389
00:17:02,188 --> 00:17:03,606
<b>of a powerful enough
cutting torch,</b>

390
00:17:03,648 --> 00:17:05,984
<b>it wouldn't matter how thick
the safe was.</b>

391
00:17:06,526 --> 00:17:08,319
<b>He has a cutting torch!</b>

392
00:17:08,361 --> 00:17:09,403
<b>I'm finished!</b>

393
00:17:09,529 --> 00:17:10,947
<b>He can just wait
until I fall asleep,</b>

394
00:17:10,989 --> 00:17:13,031
<b>sneak in with his torch,
burn through the safe door,</b>

395
00:17:13,073 --> 00:17:15,201
<b>and walk away
with my 200 million!</b>

396
00:17:15,242 --> 00:17:16,619
<b>Well, not on my watch!</b>

397
00:17:16,661 --> 00:17:17,787
<b>[Nao gasps]</b>

398
00:17:20,456 --> 00:17:22,667
<b>[Fujisawa grunting]</b>

399
00:17:23,209 --> 00:17:25,003
<b>[FUJISAWA] Come on and try me,
young blood.</b>

400
00:17:25,043 --> 00:17:26,504
<b>You want to cut open my safe?</b>

401
00:17:26,546 --> 00:17:28,882
<b>Then I'll cut you open
with my kitchen knives!</b>

402
00:17:28,923 --> 00:17:30,048
<b>[Nao breathes uneasily]</b>

403
00:17:30,090 --> 00:17:32,343
<b>[chuckles] What the hell?</b>

404
00:17:32,385 --> 00:17:33,803
<b>[FUJISAWA] Wait a second.</b>

405
00:17:33,845 --> 00:17:36,180
<b>Even if he had some
industrial grade cutting torch,</b>

406
00:17:36,222 --> 00:17:37,891
<b>at the very least,
it'll take him</b>

407
00:17:37,932 --> 00:17:40,226
<b>the better part of an hour
to get that safe open.</b>

408
00:17:40,267 --> 00:17:42,311
<b>It would be a lot faster
and more practical</b>

409
00:17:42,353 --> 00:17:44,772
<b>to simply carry it off somewhere
and destroy it!</b>

410
00:17:44,814 --> 00:17:46,566
<b>So that's his game!</b>

411
00:17:48,526 --> 00:17:50,028
<b>[Akiyama chuckles]</b>

412
00:17:50,110 --> 00:17:53,489
<b>What unhinged thing is your
paranoia telling you to do now?</b>

413
00:17:53,531 --> 00:17:54,991
<b>[Fujisawa grunting]</b>

414
00:17:57,744 --> 00:17:59,871
<b>What's going on over there?</b>

415
00:17:59,913 --> 00:18:01,664
<b>Pretty sure
he's securing the safe</b>

416
00:18:01,706 --> 00:18:03,123
<b>so we can't carry it off.</b>

417
00:18:03,666 --> 00:18:06,293
<b>I'm afraid it's too little,
too late.</b>

418
00:18:07,003 --> 00:18:09,171
<b>[NAO] There was still
a lot of uncertainty,</b>

419
00:18:09,213 --> 00:18:11,758
<b>but I was grateful
for Akiyama's confidence.</b>

420
00:18:12,550 --> 00:18:14,010
<b>If not for that,</b>

421
00:18:14,176 --> 00:18:17,722
<b>I know I would've fallen apart
like Mr. Fujisawa by that point.</b>

422
00:18:18,932 --> 00:18:20,224
<b>That was day 25.</b>

423
00:18:20,266 --> 00:18:21,517
<b>LIAR GAME ENDS IN 4 DAYS</b>

424
00:18:21,559 --> 00:18:23,853
<b>Only four more left until
the game was over.</b>

425
00:18:23,895 --> 00:18:25,145
<b>[lock clicks]</b>

426
00:18:25,187 --> 00:18:26,480
<b>[Fujisawa grunts]</b>

427
00:18:27,189 --> 00:18:28,775
<b>[Fujisawa panting]</b>

428
00:18:30,484 --> 00:18:31,611
<b>[Fujisawa gasps]</b>

429
00:18:31,861 --> 00:18:34,154
<b>WE WILL COLLECT THE MONEY
AT 5:00 PM ON JUNE 14TH.</b>

430
00:18:36,449 --> 00:18:39,368
<b>[FUJISAWA] We've reached
the beginning of the end.</b>

431
00:18:39,410 --> 00:18:41,203
<b>[Fujisawa chuckles]</b>

432
00:18:41,245 --> 00:18:43,790
<b>If I can hold it together
for just 90 more hours,</b>

433
00:18:43,831 --> 00:18:46,124
<b>I'll win 100 million yen!</b>

434
00:18:46,166 --> 00:18:48,210
<b>[NAO] I saw this
in the mail today.</b>

435
00:18:48,252 --> 00:18:50,797
<b>No doubt they sent him
the same announcement.</b>

436
00:18:51,422 --> 00:18:54,258
<b>In four days, at 5:00 p.m.</b>

437
00:18:54,508 --> 00:18:55,635
<b>What now?</b>

438
00:18:55,676 --> 00:18:57,971
<b>I can't just keep watching him,
can I?</b>

439
00:18:58,012 --> 00:19:00,598
<b>You're doing exactly
what you need to.</b>

440
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:01,933
<b>By watching Fujisawa,</b>

441
00:19:01,975 --> 00:19:03,935
<b>you're pushing him
in the right direction.</b>

442
00:19:03,977 --> 00:19:05,061
<b>Am I?</b>

443
00:19:05,103 --> 00:19:06,437
<b>Stop worrying.</b>

444
00:19:06,479 --> 00:19:09,690
<b>You see, I've already cast
a spell on that safe.</b>

445
00:19:09,983 --> 00:19:13,444
<b>And when the time comes,
it's gonna swing wide open.</b>

446
00:19:13,486 --> 00:19:14,946
<b>[NAO] Huh?</b>

447
00:19:16,030 --> 00:19:19,241
<b>LIAR GAME ENDS IN 3 DAYS</b>

448
00:19:19,951 --> 00:19:22,202
<b>[FUJISAWA]
Only three days to go.</b>

449
00:19:22,745 --> 00:19:26,499
<b>Just 72 hours
between me and millions.</b>

450
00:19:27,041 --> 00:19:30,294
<b>LIAR GAME ENDS IN 2 DAYS</b>

451
00:19:32,797 --> 00:19:36,009
<b>LIAR GAME ENDS IN 23 HOURS</b>

452
00:19:36,509 --> 00:19:39,804
<b>LIAR GAME ENDS IN 12 HOURS</b>

453
00:19:40,763 --> 00:19:42,849
<b>Twelve hours before the end.</b>

454
00:19:43,516 --> 00:19:45,518
<b>Was Akiyama telling the truth?</b>

455
00:19:45,559 --> 00:19:47,145
<b>Will it really open?</b>

456
00:19:48,062 --> 00:19:50,982
<b>LIAR GAME ENDS IN 5 HOURS</b>

457
00:19:51,024 --> 00:19:53,067
<b>Not much longer now.</b>

458
00:19:53,109 --> 00:19:54,819
<b>I can't drop the ball here.</b>

459
00:19:54,861 --> 00:19:58,698
<b>Nothing is going to keep me
from getting what's mine.</b>

460
00:20:01,075 --> 00:20:04,829
<b>LIAR GAME ENDS IN...</b>

461
00:20:07,414 --> 00:20:10,877
<b>...55 MINUTES</b>

462
00:20:11,585 --> 00:20:14,088
<b>It's too late!
I'm going to lose!</b>

463
00:20:14,130 --> 00:20:15,381
<b>[Fujisawa gasps]</b>

464
00:20:15,464 --> 00:20:18,216
<b>[NAO] Akiyama, where are you?
I need your help!</b>

465
00:20:18,258 --> 00:20:19,844
<b>The game is almost over!</b>

466
00:20:19,886 --> 00:20:21,179
<b>Please, I don't know what to do!</b>

467
00:20:21,219 --> 00:20:23,263
<b>Akiyama, you said
the safe would open,</b>

468
00:20:23,305 --> 00:20:25,016
<b>but it still hasn't!</b>

469
00:20:25,391 --> 00:20:26,976
<b>[Fujisawa gasps]</b>

470
00:20:27,018 --> 00:20:28,268
<b>[Fujisawa chuckles]</b>

471
00:20:28,519 --> 00:20:29,603
<b>[Nao gasps]</b>

472
00:20:29,645 --> 00:20:31,355
<b>[Fujisawa laughs]</b>

473
00:20:31,397 --> 00:20:32,899
<b>I knew you were bluffing!</b>

474
00:20:32,940 --> 00:20:34,232
<b>You were just trying to trick me</b>

475
00:20:34,274 --> 00:20:35,902
<b>into thinking
you could open the safe!</b>

476
00:20:35,943 --> 00:20:38,362
<b>Please, Mr. Fujisawa...</b>

477
00:20:38,404 --> 00:20:41,074
<b>I know I've been spying on you
and scaring you this whole time,</b>

478
00:20:41,115 --> 00:20:43,826
<b>and I'm sorry,
but you don't have to do this!</b>

479
00:20:43,868 --> 00:20:44,911
<b>We'll both be safe</b>

480
00:20:44,952 --> 00:20:47,329
<b>if you give me
my 100 million back.</b>

481
00:20:47,371 --> 00:20:51,000
<b>[cries] Please, Mr. Fujisawa.
Don't do this.</b>

482
00:20:51,042 --> 00:20:53,377
<b>Please, Mr. Fujisawa.</b>

483
00:20:53,419 --> 00:20:54,921
<b>You can save me
and my family,</b>

484
00:20:54,962 --> 00:20:57,339
<b>-if you just help me!
-[grunts] Shut up!</b>

485
00:20:57,381 --> 00:20:58,716
<b>[Nao grunts]</b>

486
00:20:58,758 --> 00:20:59,884
<b>Mr. Fujisawa!</b>

487
00:20:59,926 --> 00:21:01,468
<b>[Fujisawa scoffs]</b>

488
00:21:02,929 --> 00:21:05,139
<b>[Nao cries]</b>

489
00:21:05,181 --> 00:21:07,975
<b>[NAO] No, open the door!
Open the door! Open the door!</b>

490
00:21:08,017 --> 00:21:10,477
<b>Please, Mr. Fujisawa!
Don't do this to me.</b>

491
00:21:10,519 --> 00:21:12,188
<b>-[chuckles]
-There's still time!</b>

492
00:21:12,230 --> 00:21:14,272
<b>Forty-five minutes left
and counting!</b>

493
00:21:14,314 --> 00:21:16,776
<b>Help me! Please, help me!</b>

494
00:21:16,817 --> 00:21:18,694
<b>Mr. Fujisawa, help me!</b>

495
00:21:18,736 --> 00:21:21,321
<b>You're better than this! Please!</b>

496
00:21:21,948 --> 00:21:24,200
<b>[FUJISAWA] Thirty minutes
and counting!</b>

497
00:21:24,992 --> 00:21:28,746
<b>[clock ticking]</b>

498
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:34,961
<b>[FUJISAWA] Ten minutes!</b>

499
00:21:37,463 --> 00:21:40,758
<b>[NAO] Please...
There's still time.</b>

500
00:21:40,800 --> 00:21:42,260
<b>Don't do this.</b>

501
00:21:43,261 --> 00:21:45,805
<b>[FUJISAWA] One minute left!</b>

502
00:21:45,846 --> 00:21:47,807
<b>[ticking continues]</b>

503
00:21:50,559 --> 00:21:57,441
<b>[FUJISAWA]
Eight, seven, six, five, four,</b>

504
00:21:57,483 --> 00:22:02,071
<b>three, two, one!</b>

505
00:22:02,362 --> 00:22:04,573
<b>I did it!</b>

506
00:22:04,615 --> 00:22:08,410
<b>-I won the game!
-[Nao screams] No!</b>

507
00:22:09,620 --> 00:22:11,998
<b>[doorbell rings]</b>

508
00:22:15,417 --> 00:22:17,920
<b>[♪ closing theme song playing]</b>

509
00:23:44,882 --> 00:23:49,929
<b>NEXT TIME
RESOLUTION</b>

